emale":"Deceased","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1118":"1118","about 1162":"about 1162","1301":"1301","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","before 1197":"before 1197","1197":"1197","before 1162":"before 1162","1162":"1162","1208":"1208","abt. 1197":"about 1197","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Europe":"Europe","Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland","of Pury Ogilvy, Forfar, Sctl.":"Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ogilvie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Oglesby  , a habitational name from the barony of Ogilvie in Glamis (Angus), whose name is probably Pictish, of uncertain origin and meaning.","Irish: adopted for   Gilboy  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Oglesby","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: habitational name from the barony of Ogilvie in Glamis, Angus, whose name is probably Pictish, of uncertain origin and meaning.","History: A Scottish family of this name descend from Gilibride, Earl of Angus (died <i>c.</i> 1187), whose son Gilbert was granted the lands of <i>Ogguluin</i> (Ogilvie) in the late 12th century. <i>Ogilvie</i> was also the name of a barony in Banffshire, but that took its name from the surname."]}]},{"name":"Gilbride","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan.","Scottish (Midlothian): variant of   Kilbride  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kilbride","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Kieran, Aidan.","Irish (Connacht) and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Giolla Brighde</b> (Irish) or <b>Mac Gille Brighde</b> (Scottish) ‘son of the servant of (Saint) Brigit’, also often shortened and Anglicized as   McBride  . The name <i>Brigit</i> means ‘exalted’. Brigit was originally a pagan goddess, many of whose attributes, such as a sacred fire, became attached to the historical figure of Saint Brigit of Kildare (452–523), founder of the first Irish convent.","Scottish: habitational name from any of various places with this name, from Gaelic <i>Cill Bríghde</i> ‘church of Saint Brigit’ (<i>cill</i> being from Latin <i>cella</i> ‘room, cell’), for example Kilbride in Lanarkshire."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gilbride Ogilvie II was born about 1162, in Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland as the son of Gilbride Earl of Angus and wife Gilbride Earl of Angus. He married Maud before 1197, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland."},"et":{"about 1162–":"umbes 1162–Surnud","1162–Male":"1162–Surnud","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1208–1301":"1208–1301","–Female":"Surnud","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1118":"1118","about 1162":"umbes 1162","1301":"1301","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","before 1197":"enne 1197","1197":"1197","before 1162":"enne 1162","1162":"1162","1208":"1208","abt. 1197":"umbes 1197","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Europe":"Europe","Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland","of Pury Ogilvy, Forfar, Sctl.":"Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1162–":"noin 1162–Kuollut","1162–Male":"1162–Kuollut","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","1197–Male":"1197–Kuollut","1208–1301":"1208–1301","–Female":"Kuollut","1118–1187":"1118–1187","1118":"1118","about 1162":"noin 1162","1301":"1301","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","before 1197":"ennen vuotta 1197","1197":"1197","before 1162":"ennen vuotta 1162","1162":"1162","1208":"1208","abt. 1197":"noin 1197","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Forfar, Forfarshire, Scotland","Europe":"Europe","Milton of Ogilvie, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Milton of Ogilvie, Forfars